<tr>
<td><a href="UltraBoard.cgi?Action=ShowProfile&ID=elementalist&Board=shadow&Idle=30&Sort=0&Order=Descend&Page=0&Session=" target="Profile" OnMouseOver="window.status='View elementalist (elementalist) Profile.';return true;" OnMouseOut="window.status=''"><font face="Verdana" size="1" color="000000 ">Profile</font></a></td><td align="RIGHT"></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="EEEEEE">
<td><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="5" cellpadding="5" align="CENTER">
<tr>
<td valign="MIDDLE"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="000000">i play a pally and love the ability to lay hands. there is no greater feeling then seeing your buddy get knocked unconsous lay hands on them ans see them pop back up again. or save them when they are running from a train...<p>

but i must say, SK's should be exact opposite of pally's.  I heal them to run, SK's should nuke them (killing the baddy) so their friends will live.  at lvl 50 i can lay hands for more then 2000 HP, an SK only HT for 600 HP which is pathetic.  Any creature lvl 45 + has more than 5 k of life (casters not included)  600 dmg won't even get the mob to aggro on you so your friend can run.  I almost restarted as an SK because i thought they were better, but my pally has grown on me.  <p>

over all lets taka a poll of HT vs LH in a group ans solo.<p>

when in a group would you rather get somebody to nuke for 600 dmg (when a wiz can do twice that) or a pally heal 2 k + of life?<p>

i take the pally.<p>

when solo'ing when you are close to death, you want to be able to nuke for 600 dmg or heal yourself full?<p>

i take the heal.<p>

but in other area's SK's are stronger.  they get cooler spells, and can make a pet (even if it is really bad).  Everything else is pretty much the same, SK's and pally's i think are very even except when it comes to their special talents...HT and LH.<p>

Verant really should make HT more powerful just to even the classes out.<p>

just my 2 cp worth and sorry for the long post.</font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="DDDDDD">
