<td><a href="UltraBoard.cgi?Action=ShowProfile&ID=uzzel&Board=shadow&Idle=30&Sort=0&Order=Descend&Page=0&Session=" target="Profile" OnMouseOver="window.status='View SKGuy (uzzel) Profile.';return true;" OnMouseOut="window.status=''"><font face="Verdana" size="1" color="000000 ">Profile</font></a></td><td align="RIGHT"></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="EEEEEE">
<td><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="5" cellpadding="5" align="CENTER">
<tr>
<td valign="MIDDLE"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="000000">This is a common discussion among Pally and sk's. I have a 40 ESK. I believe that these classes are balanced. Is HT equal to LoH? No, but I dont even think it should. At early levels, this helps the sk get to 30, where a sk starts to get powerful. At higher levels, yes, mobs have MUCh more hp, but that is 600dmg that is not planned on, that is instant. 2000hp heal better? Not all the time. If a group is weakened and get a pop they didnt expect, everyone lom, HT is much more valuable. Yes, you can save one with the heal, but what if the mob has ae dd or the like? It is better to kill it as fast as possible, IMO.<p>

As far as solo, depending on the mob, and sk will solo better than a pally. Not to discredit pally at all, but a good sk wont even get hit much. At 40, I can solo in Overthere without losing more than a bub of health...oom:), but only losing 1 bub of health. Heals in solo for Pally are more difficult and every time it is interrupted, that is more damage you are taking. I would say pally have a shorter downtime as the heals are great after a fight. Also these opinions are only what I have observed as I have never played a pally.<p>

I think that doing straight compairisons of pally vs sk is not accurate. The higher the level, the more different they become. Rather than saying LoH is better than HT, look at it from a whole class view. <p>

How ironic that a combo of sk/pally for a 2 man group is QUITE powerful!:)</font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="DDDDDD">
