<td valign="MIDDLE"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="000000">Oh yeah, one more thing to add: the reason making HT do 1/2 the damage of LH would unbalance everything is that, in a duel, that would actually make the Pally EASIER to kill than if neither skill existed. Ie. the Pally knows your HT is gonna take half his hp, so he has to use LH at 51% hp or greater to prolong the fight. So you take 49% of his energy, he uses his LH to refill to max, you take 50% again then HT him...dead Pally. You have now just killed him by taking 99% of his hp instead of 100%. The 2 skills would be negated, and the whole duel would just degenerate into who can deal out the most melee/spell damage fastest.<p>

And, obviously, all other classes would have no prayer of taking an SK in an even-level duel.<p>

Verant didnt create the skills arbitrarily. You can be sure that the skills as they are now are as balanced as they can possibly get. If you find your skillset inadequate, you are not making the most of what you have. Either choose a new class, or learn to play smarter.<p>

My 2cp</font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="DDDDDD">
