<td valign="MIDDLE"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="000000">Not sure how many of you SKs have played paladins, but my short exp to lvl 9 with a pally taught me a lot.  When comparing the two, HT vs LH, people tend to forget that LH has a casting time and can be interrupted.  Its not to likely to be interrupted but it is still a factor.  If the last post is true and LH isn't simply a complete heal, which I've always known it to be then that makes it even less of a powerful skill.  Whether or not the last post was true, what I know to be true is that at lvl 49 Shadowknights can use a quest spell that drains, does damage and heals you for those who are unsure, 280 HPs.  Thats almost half a HT at that lvl plus it heals you.  I'm not sure how much mana it takes to cast or how many times you can cast it with average int, but when you add it up, if we can cast it 5 times (1400 dmg drained) add it to HT (600 dmg) that equals 2000 total dmg, plus we drain 1400 life which is prolly over half our life.  I hope this clears things up, and if anyone questions the power of a SK this should help the argument.  However if any High Lvl SKs find that I am wrong or agree with me, Please Post.  I'm lvl 39 and know only what my high lvl (51 + ) SK friends tell me. Kind of a long post, thanks for reading :O)<hr>Kyree ShadowMaster</font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="DDDDDD">
