<td valign="MIDDLE"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="000000">Ive seen alot of people complaining about how Verant is screwing SKs over.  Well, I think that is untrue.  Granted, HT is well, not worth very much...but I wouldnt say it was worthless.  600 dmg is better than nothing.  So HT isnt as good as LoH, does that really matter?  Personaly, Id rather play a SK without HT than a Pally with LoH.  Why?  Because LoH is only usable once every 90min!  So every once in a while a Pally can heal someone completely...clerics get spells that can do that all the time, so long as they have the mana.  And when you look at all other areas between the SK and the Pally, the SK owns.  The SK can do more damage with pets and life steals (at upper levels for the life steals), and they get debuffs!  All Pallys get are heals and buffs.  Oh, and Pallys cant fear kitt ;).  Pallys may get LoH, but lets face it SKs can do more damage and jsut plain take more out of an opponent than a Pally will ever be able to.  Period.<p>

<br>
PS:  I ahve nothing against Pallys, and actually the classes are quite balanced ;).  actually think SKs are a bit more powerful than Pallys...or at least a bit more useful.  But then again SKs have faction problems.</font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="DDDDDD">
