<td valign="MIDDLE"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="000000">Someone here mentioned that Paladin's LOH recycles every 90 minutes. And for that reason he would prefer a SK in his group.A little news flash: HT also takes that long to recycle! <br>
HT should be more powerful. At my current level (35) I do about 320 damage. Is that a lot? Compare it to LOH. I don't have a pally, but I observed a few. <br>
Consider this (approximation of a level 35 character) : Paladin attacks a high blue con. He does 1000 damage before he's taken down to 1 bubble. He LOH. He regains all or most of his health allowing him to fight the mob and quite possibly damage it for another 1000 points. <br>
SK is fighting the same mob. He does 1000 damage just like the paladin in the fight earlier, before he's taken down to 1 bubble. He HT's the mob. If it's not resisted he causes about 320 damage to the mob. Since the mob still has a lot of hit points to throw around the sk now has 3 choices: fight on and die, FD or run away.<br>
This places HT in different perspective. It's no longer that "powerful", now is it?<br>
Someone else said that if HT was more powerful, a group of SK's could HT a high level mob to death. I have read that before. Over a year ago one of VI's employees posted that on a EQ web site. Here is what is wrong with that thinking: Go ahead and run up to a mob that is red to you. Just 4 or 5 levels. HT it. See how the mob easily resists all your pitiful HT damage, calmly turns around and rips you to little SK shreds. Red to high? OK, do the same thing to a yellow. It will resist at least 50% of your HT damage. If the mob has at least 2000 hp's, like most at  my level do, 6 sk's could not even take it's health down by 50%...<br>
Now before you start shouting and screaming like little kindergartners saying: "NOT MY SK, YOU FREAK!", YES YOUR SK TOO! <p>

Another thing that I'd like to mention:<br>
The main thing that supposed to make SK's powerful is the addition of a pet. Now how many of you have actually used SK's pet in a dungeon? There is no point to try to convince anyone that you have successfully done so. Give it a try. Your pet will attract all the mobs in the area. It's like waving a big red sign that says: Over here! Come and ambush my group! They were dumb enough to allow the SK to summon a pet!<br>
I don't want the SK pet to be more powerful, but the idea is that it should con about even with it's owner. The pet can not mop up hit points like a SK would. It wasn't meant to. It's a long lasting DOT. Good fear factor in duels, and extra bit of damage when soloing. The damage it does right now is "balanced". But it needs to have it's mob con set higher.</font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="DDDDDD">
<td><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" align="CENTER">
