<tr>
<td valign="MIDDLE"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="000000">I do want to start a food fight but...<p>

Lets do a quick match up of SK's vs Paladins:<p>

Paladin.<br>
Pros:    Can heal himself or others. <br>
            Can buff himself or others.<br>
            Can dish out just as much melee damage as a SK.<br>
            LOH.<br>
            Not much of a faction problem in most cities in Norrath.<br>
            Has some combat related spells that come in very handy, e.g..: Flash of light.<br>
            High level class specific armor is better than that of SK's<br>
            Welcomed in groups.<p>

Cons:    Not as good at dealing melee damage as a warrior.<br>
            Spells  tend to be mostly defensive or healing oriented.<br>
            No pet.<br>
            <p>

SK.<br>
Pros:    Dishes more or less the same melee damage as a Paladin.<br>
            Low level but rather nasty dot spells.<br>
            Pet.<br>
            HT             <br>
            It's easier to obtain certain class oriented items that it is for Paladins.<br>
            Feign Death.<br>
            Can fear kite rather well.<br>
            <br>
Cons:    Can do very limited self healing, e.g..: Vamiric embrace, misc. health siphon spells.<br>
            Limited buffs, mostly disease, cold resistance oriented.<br>
            Major faction problems.<br>
            Armor not as good as that of Paladins.<br>
            Spells are mostly offensive oriented.<br>
            Spells resisted very often at later levels.<br>
            HT resisted a lot at later levels.<br>
            Because of it's level pet becomes liability in dungeons and in crowded areas.<br>
            Not as popular in groups.<p>

And just for the sake of it I'll add one more class to this:<p>

Rouge.<br>
Pros.    Dishes obscene amount of damage.<br>
            CAN fear kite with appropriate equipment.<br>
            Can hide and move at the same time, i.e.: invisibility.<br>
            Can take a fair amount of damage.<br>
            Backstab.<br>
            Class specific items are rather easy to obtain.<br>
            Can gain access to areas where no one else can.<p>

Cons:    No plate armor (except for the planar that looks like plate)<br>
            No spells.<br>
            No pet.<br>
            <p>

In my opinion (fell free to disagree, this is democracy, or so I've been told about the sandy, turkey eating, cactus infested, cowboy overrun country down south...)<br>
SK's have more cons to deal with than pros. I used to be very pro SK. But now after playing for a while I've noticed the shortcomings of the class. <p>

On another note. My advice to people considering the class: Loose the small and medium races. You're not supposed to be a good caster. In a group that's all taken care of. No one wants average quality tank in their group. The casters are supposed to nuke and heal while you are supposed to tank and taunt the mob off them.<br>
At later levels most people group. If you're planning on soloing for all your life you can forget about planar raids and good equipment. I've chosen human because of the better faction and no race experience penalty. Now I'm kicking myself over the head. Was misa tinkin?! The advantages of being a large race are enormous. Yes, they are dumb at first. But I have seen ogres with all skills, including INT, way above mine with proper equipment. Large races can take a lot of punishment and dish it out too. Yes, inkies look nice in their horned skull helmets. Do what? They suck at tanking as much as humans and erudies do.</font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="DDDDDD">
