<td valign="MIDDLE"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="000000">Ganedorf,  everyone has his own opinion and a different point of view. <br>
But to place it in a different perspective: Yes you can dish out damage with your spells, Great!<br>
Guess what, that Forest Giant will take to liking you a lot. What happens then? Without a good defense (for example: buffs) youre f*cked. So here you are dishing out damage. But you cant take it yourself. <br>
So you HT it, right? The forest Giant looks down at you, scratches his a*s before shaking off 80% of your HT and calmly tears your head off. <br>
Never underestimate good defense. Youre a tank. You supposed to be mopping damage so that the other, weaker classes dont have to. They do the real damage after all. Your pitiful 500 points of damage during a fight is nothing comparing to a casters (a wizard will fry that mob 10 times over before you do any actual damage to it). Defense is more important.<br>
So you can fear Kite. Good. How long do you think youll be doing that? Eventually you will have to group. And fear kiting will become less and less feasible. Last thing you want to do if fear something in a dungeon (man, I dare you...).<br>
Im glad you like inkies. They are a challenge to play. If you like being hated in most zones of Norrath and being weak, all the power to you. Inkies make great casters, but only mediocre tanks. Large races are hated also mind you, but they are nowhere near being weak. With proper items they can bump their INT way up there so there goes your INT advantage out the window.<br>
Inkies look sweet in armor, Ill give them that. But they do not make good tanks.<br>
Still like I said, everyone is entitled to his or her own opinion.<p>

May Innoruuk or whatever god you believe have mercy on your soul.</font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="DDDDDD">
