<tr>
<td valign="MIDDLE"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="000000">Have you tried fearing anything blue or above lately? Have you noticed how fast your Fear breaks?<br>
Or how about one of the Darkness spells? They break so fast you wont even have the time pick your nose<br>
When you run out of mana, and you will rather quickly, the mob will go after you, making you hurt plenty.<br>
Do this. Create a dummy Ogre SK. Look at his stats and then pump the extra points into INT. Youll see the advantage the ogre has. With starting STR of about 140+ and 130+ STAM  (Im not exactly sure these are the precise numbers, its been a while, correct me if Im wrong) ogre player only needs to increase his INT and maybe DEX with items. He will actually get decent INT. On the other hand youll be far behind with STR and STAM.<br>
I think youre under the delusion that youre a caster. You are not a caster. Youre a damage sponge, a tank.<br>
Your spells dont amount to much when grouped. Sure you can throw your obscure spells at the mob, just for that extra illusion that youre useful to the group. Maybe darkness a running mob. But in reality its the casters who do the damage, not you.<br>
Ive played small, medium and large races. And one thing that I learned is that a large race is way more brutal in a fight. They are not as dependant on spells as are the smaller races. And with the proper equipment they will outcast a human or an inkie or even an erudi (these guys have hell of a mana pool, but crappy STR and other stats. They have to focus their extra points and items on the other stats)<br>
In one of my posts above I gave you example of a soloing character (the Paladin and SK soloing a Giant). The tables even out when youre grouped. On the other hand anyone will become way more powerful when grouped. A warrior alone is decent. He can take on stuff that an SK will not touch. But he has a long down time (like any other class that cant heal themselves). Place him in a group with a cleric, a shaman or enchanter. All of the sudden that warrior turns into a pure killing machine. He will also mop up those hits like there is no tomorrow. A paladin, SK, monk, etc will also become more powerful. But while the paladins spells are a welcomed addition to the group, youll be arguing with the others about whos snare is better. Your pitiful spells and dots dont amount to much (maybe blood boil or heart flutter are the exception). In the end youll end up just STR leaching the mob hoping that it was actually affected by your spell.<br>
Fear spell becomes a liability once in dungeons. Thats where youll spend the other half of your life. And last thing you want is fearing something in a dungeon. <br>
Large races have their faults too. They are big. What this means is that and ogre or troll in a narrow corridor in a dungeon spells death to anyone trying to escape from a frenzied mob.<br>
Anyhow. Enough of me ranting. Take care.</font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="DDDDDD">
