<td valign="MIDDLE"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="000000">Firstly, Dune, as a de sk, neither ogre nor troll SK, Shaman or Warrior has never interrupted my casts.  The only class that has managed interrupt me in duels is a ranger, but they couldn't prevent me from shadowstepping.  Which then became a moot point because I could cast against them without fear of interruption until they got to me.  Biggest misconception is that big races are best duelers.  Sorry,  big races make for big targets. ;)<p>

Secondly, and back to the point, LH vs HT.  Sadly, HT isn't as effective as it should.  LH is hardly ever resisted.  Try HT on some red or yellow mobs, sometimes you get a full resist, sometimes its partial, rarely do you get full damage.  I've even seen greens resist.   I would like to see HT damage increased and resistance dropped since it is a class defining ability.  The theory of 6 SK's getting together to HT an ubermob is silly.  Let's substitute a different class for SK, um, Wizards.  6 Wizards casting spells that can do up to 1200 points.  or, Druids, that can cast up to 1024 points of damage each.  Or, Necros who can do up to 1100 damage.  Let's also realize that these other classes can keep casting as long as they have mana whereas a sk has to wait for 90 minutes for next use.  You see how the scenario is a farce YET I did see Verant use it to justify the HT at its present state.</font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="DDDDDD">
