<td valign="MIDDLE"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="000000">I find it odd that everyone complains about resists.  When I was a young SK (going into and through the 20's) I felt that it got over resisted.  Often on blues and I wouldn't even use it on black or yellows because they never stuck.  I remember I was overjoyed when I got a half resist on a yellow con, Broon.  <p>

But when I got near thirty I noticed a change.  My HT started sticking on stuff.  I was fighting cyclops and giant skellies in Rathe mountains and it stuck like 10 times no resists.  I thought I was the luckiest SK alive.  Then one night our group wanted to fight Cynthia.  She conned yellow to me so I wouldn't think about using HT on her.  But when she nuked the druid down to one bubble of health I HTed her.  Full damage on a yellow!  My 300 point nuke really too a chunk out of her.  We killed her 2 more times that night that I had HT and they stuck completely on her every time.  My group always felt safer knowing I had that up since things can get bad really quickly with her.  (That was probably one of the most fun night for me on EQ.  And I know the group feels the same)  When my group broke up and it was just me and the cleric a HG group needed a healer so we joined them even though we were low 30's.  I got a full HT one a HG too!  I couldn't believe it.  But anyway since then my HT has had very very few resists.  Sometimes I'll get a partial resist on a blue but rarely.  And It almost always sticks for full even on yellows and reds.  I remember a Gnoll partial resisted one.  The sarnak who drops the Jade prod got 1 partial and I got one to stick for full on him  (I was around 43 I think).  Vox got a full resist.  But other than that I've had good luck with it.  I'm not sure if I'm really lucky, or if they changed something, or if it has something to do with my stats.  High int?  I even have had many full HTs on red cons.  Like the black widow in dreadlands.  I'm not sure why it's been working so well for me but I've been happy with it.</font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="DDDDDD">
