<td><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="5" cellpadding="5" align="CENTER">
<tr>
<td valign="MIDDLE"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="000000">Hi Dune.  Sorry, I didn't miss your point at all.  BTW, I play on TZ. ;)<p>

1. With super high magic resistance your spells would not stick, or they would only last a second.<p>

Most of the spells I've cast have stuck on even people with high mr.  I took on a druid who was my senior in levels and I was able to land darkness 1 time out of 7.  I would like to also mention that he never once resisted my tap, syphon, vortex, or dots.  The only thing that damn druid had on me was levels and high damage DDs.<p>

2. I see you have fought with people who dont know how to duel (except for the ranger).<br>
With a fast hitting weapon, bash, slam and a bow an ogre or a troll would make a short work of you.<br>
In a duel, against a fast moving, casting target a slow, had hitting weapon is a hindrance.<p>

You presume a lot about the people I fight and my own skills.  In fights, you have to always make adjustments based on what your opponent is capable of doing.  If they are casting, then a good shield and weapon combo is needed to deal with that, but if they are meleeing then a high damage 2h-weapon is better for the jousting that will ensue.  Being a smaller race, I do agree that toe-to-toe combat is not in best interest unless it's down to the wire.<p>

3. This is not real life, a large race or a small race makes the same target. There is no difference.<p>

No, there you are wrong.  There is a difference in perspective which does affect combat.  If you have ever played a large class, you will know that sometimes a npc or player can get into a position where you are able to see them but can't hit them.  Also, in a duel you are constantly moving around, moving through, etc.  If you are standing still, doing toe-to-toe fight, then you are not using your size advantage.<p>

4. Youre also forgetting that you wouldnt be dueling a pansy ranger, but someone with the same abilities as you. <br>
All SKs get the same spells (yes, even Shadowstep, doh!).<p>

In a duel, it's not the class but the person that is important.  Against a SK of my level, I have no doubt that I will come out the winner.  I'm just that good. ;)</font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="DDDDDD">
