<td><a href="UltraBoard.cgi?Action=ShowProfile&ID=dune&Board=shadow&Idle=30&Sort=0&Order=Descend&Page=0&Session=" target="Profile" OnMouseOver="window.status='View Dune (dune) Profile.';return true;" OnMouseOut="window.status=''"><font face="Verdana" size="1" color="000000 ">Profile</font></a></td><td align="RIGHT"></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="EEEEEE">
<td><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="5" cellpadding="5" align="CENTER">
<tr>
<td valign="MIDDLE"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="000000">Well, the druid obviously forgot to bump up his magic resistance.<br>
Ive taken on druids before. Most of them relay on their speed and kite advantage.<br>
In a fight they will try to snare you, dot you and then run off. All the druids I have fought have completely disregarded their Magic resistance. Once you take away their speed advantage (Darkness spells) they are dead in the water.<br>
Now try dueling a chanter. He will debuff you so much you wont be able to move or resist anything. While youre slowed to nothing (movement, fighting, casting), his pet combined with few of his offensive spells will turn you into Steak Tar Tar (my favorite food btw).<p>

I never assume anything. I never underestimate an opponent, that leads to lost duel. <p>

As for perspective, thats what the mouse is for. Use it to look around and move. <br>
If someone or something gets into a position where a player or a NPC cant hit it its called an exploit. Punishable by frozen accounts or cancellation.<p>

Yes, a smart player is more important than a class. But two smart players playing the same class can be very dangerous to each other. Never assume that the player behind the character is a moron. He could be just as good or better than you (and there always is). All people use different fighting techniques, no duel will ever be the same unless youre fighting against a bunch of newbies. <p>

No one is that good, NO ONE. <p>

Anyway, my two silver. Have fun and kill something for Innruuk.</font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="DDDDDD">
